<cshelp id="storage" xml:lang="en-us">
<title>Storage</title>
<shortdesc>The <wintitle>Storage</wintitle> page shows information
about host system storage information.</shortdesc>
<csbody>
<p>Use these sections to configure storage of the host system.</p>
<dl><dlentry>
<dt>Volume Group</dt>
<dd>LVM (logical volume management) provides a method of allocating space on mass-storage devices that is more flexible than conventional partitioning schemes.</dd>
<dd>Supporting operations on Volume Groups.</dd>
<dd>* Listing</dd>
</dlentry>
<dlentry>
<dt>File Systems</dt>
<dd>File system used to control how data stored and retrieved from storage device.</dd>
<dd>* Listing </dd>
</dlentry>
<dlentry>
<dt>Swap Devices</dt>
<dd>Swap device is repository of memory segments that are paged out of physical RAM. Swap space can be of type partition or of type file.</dd>
<dd>* Listing </dd>
</dlentry>
<dlentry>
<dt>Storage Devices</dt>
<dd>Storage device is any computing hardware that is used for storing, porting and extracting data files and objects.</dd>
<dd>* Listing FCP/ECKD (DASD) devices</dd>
</dlentry>
<dlentry>
<dt>SAN Adapters</dt>
<dd>A SAN Adapter is IO device used to connect to the remote SAN storage devices.</dd>
<dd>* Listing SAN Adapters</dd>
</dlentry>
</dl><?Pub Caret 2101?>
</csbody>
</cshelp>
